        "title": "test: add ClawHub release candidate QA proof",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nResolves a QA coverage gap where `clawhub.npm-pack-local-release-candidate-installs` did not have an honest primary QA Lab proof path after the checklist-only wrapper was removed.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds a QA Lab script producer that only emits primary passing evidence after a candidate `.tgz` has package/build metadata and the existing Parallels npm-update lane proves fresh install plus update semantics. Missing tarball or VM prerequisites are represented as blocked evidence through `allowBlockedEvidence`, not as a false pass.\n\nAI-assisted: authored with Codex.\n\n## User Impact\n\nRelease operators get a durable QA scenario for release-candidate npm-pack install proof. The scorecard can link the existing coverage ID without counting it fulfilled unless the real candidate install/update lane succeeds.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node --import tsx test/e2e/qa-lab/plugins/clawhub-release-candidate-install.ts --artifact-base .artifacts/qa-e2e/clawhub-release-candidate-blocked` -> wrote `qa-evidence.json` with `blocked` status and primary coverage `clawhub.npm-pack-local-release-candidate-installs` when no tarball was provided.\n- `pnpm openclaw qa suite --scenario clawhub-release-candidate-checklist --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/clawhub-release-candidate-suite-blocked` -> scenario passed with blocked producer evidence, proving `allowBlockedEvidence` is honored.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-catalog.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/test-file-scenario-runner.test.ts --reporter=verbose` -> 45 tests passed.\n- `pnpm openclaw qa coverage --match 'release candidate package install' --json` -> scenario resolves as script-backed QA coverage for `clawhub.npm-pack-local-release-candidate-installs`.\n- `git diff --check` -> clean.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` -> clean after fixing timeout, checkout-build parsing, and blocked-prerequisite classification findings.\n",
